<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"><B>ITEM 7.01 REGULATION FD DISCLOSURE</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">On February 29, 2012 Zion Oil &amp; Gas, Inc.
(the &ldquo;Company&rdquo;) sent out to its stockholders and other subscribers to its database a report updating&nbsp;the status
of the Company&rsquo;s operations.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">A copy of the report is furnished with
this Current Report on Form 8-K and attached hereto as Exhibit 99.1. Exhibit 99.1 shall not be deemed &ldquo;filed&rdquo;
for purposes of Section 18 of the Securities Exchange Act of 1934, as amended (the &ldquo;Exchange Act&rdquo;), or otherwise
subject to the liabilities under that Section and shall not be deemed to be incorporated by reference into any filing of the Company
under the Securities Act of 1933, as amended, or the Exchange Act.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"><B>ITEM 9.01. FINANCIAL STATEMENTS AND EXHIBITS</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Exhibit 99.1 &ndash; Report dated February
29, 2012</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<DESCRIPTION>REPORT DATED FEBRUARY 29, 2012
<TEXT>


<HTML>
<HEAD>
     <TITLE></TITLE>
</HEAD>
<BODY STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif">

<P STYLE="margin: 0"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"><B>Zion Oil &amp; Gas Newsletter</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0"><B>Wednesday, February 29, 2012</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~~</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"><B><I>You are receiving this email
because you subscribed to the Zion Oil &amp; Gas newsletter, containing news and exploration updates from Israel. We
appreciate your interest, but if you&rsquo;re no longer interested, please click this link</I><FONT STYLE="color: #0033CC">:&nbsp;<U>unsubscribe</U></FONT></B><FONT STYLE="color: #0033CC">. </FONT></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">Dear Shareholder and/or Friend of Zion...</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">I reported last month that there has been a
&lsquo;shake-up&rsquo; in Israel&rsquo;s government departments dealing with natural resources. In mid-2011, Dr. Gardosh was appointed
Israel&rsquo;s Petroleum Commissioner on an interim basis, but there is a six-month restriction on any interim appointments. As
of January 1, 2012, Mr. Alexander Varshavsky is the new (interim) Commissioner of Petroleum Affairs and the Ministry of Infrastructure
has been renamed the Ministry of Energy and Water Resources.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><IMG SRC="pic1.jpg" ALT=""></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><B>Meeting with Israel&rsquo;s Petroleum Commissioner</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">On Sunday, February 26, 2012, as you can see
in the above photograph, I attended a meeting in Jerusalem at the Petroleum Commissioner&rsquo;s office. Also present were:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">(a) <B>Dr. Yehezkel Druckman</B> - Zion Board
Member and Commissioner of Petroleum Affairs in Israel (1995-2004) - (far right in the photo)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">(b) <B>Mr.Yossi Virzburger</B> - the head of
the Ministry of Energy and Water Resources - formerly The Ministry of Infrastructure - (sitting opposite the computer screen)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">(b) <B>Mr. Alexander Varshavsky</B> - the Commissioner
of Petroleum Affairs - Acting / Temporary - (far left in the photo).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">(c) <B>Dr. Avi Honigstein</B> (Deputy Petroleum
Commissioner) - (closest to the camera in the photo)</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">(d) <B>Mr.</B> <B>Ilan Nissim</B> - the head
of the Safety &amp; Environment Division - (behind the camera, taking the photo).</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">The meeting was cordial and we discussed Zion&rsquo;s
various plans for the coming year, including the following:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">In our <U>Jordan Valley License</U> area, the
permitting for the 2-D seismic survey (using a dynamite source) is almost completed and we expect that the survey will be performed
by the Geophysical Institute of Israel (GII) starting in mid-March 2012. (This date is an estimate and is subject to change, based
on GII&rsquo;s schedule of commitments.)This seismic acquisition should help us to further refine our plans to drill in the Jordan
Valley License area.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">With regard to our planned VSP (vertical seismic
profile) survey in our <U>Asher-Menashe License</U> area, which we plan to acquire through a third party contractor with assistance
by GII, we have been in various discussions in order to secure appropriate equipment in line with our planned schedule.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 1 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->
<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">The Israeli rig operator <B>Lapidoth</B> has
gone on public record stating that they will give Zion priority regarding any drilling rig and crew that we may require and any
other ancillary equipment that we may need from them. We are in close contact with Lapidoth and expect that they will provide us
with a drilling rig and crew, as we require.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">With regard to our <U>Joseph License</U> area,
our scientific work continues. Today, we entered into a 16 kilometer seismic acquisition contract with GII. Zion&rsquo;s Exploration
staff is also recommending that we acquire already existing seismic data and reprocess the data to more fully evaluate the geology
of the southern Joseph License area, as we explore for potential drilling prospects in this area and possibly in our abutting and
already applied-for Asher Joseph Permit Application area that borders the Mediterranean Sea.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Zion&rsquo;s current petroleum exploration
licenses are:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 6pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 0in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in; text-align: left">&bull;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify">the Joseph License (on approximately 83,000 acres)</TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 6pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 0in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in; text-align: left">&bull;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify">the Asher-Menashe License (on approximately 79,000 acres)</TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 6pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 0in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in; text-align: left">&bull;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify">the Jordan Valley License (on approximately 56,000 acres)</TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Zion&rsquo;s total license area amounts to
approximately <B><U>218,000 acres</U></B>.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">In 2011, we submitted applications to the Israeli
Petroleum Commissioner for three further exploration areas:</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 6pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 0in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in; text-align: left">&bull;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify">the Dead Sea License Application</TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 6pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 0in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in; text-align: left">&bull;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify">the Asher-Joseph Permit Application</TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin-top: 0; margin-bottom: 6pt"><TR STYLE="vertical-align: top; text-align: justify">
<TD STYLE="width: 0in"></TD><TD STYLE="width: 0.5in; text-align: left">&bull;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: justify">the Zebulun Permit Application</TD>
</TR></TABLE>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">If all of our applications are granted, the
total petroleum exploration area under Zion&rsquo;s control would be approximately <B><U>530,000 acres</U></B>.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><IMG SRC="pic2.jpg" ALT=""></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><B>The 2012 National Religious
Broadcasters Convention</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><B>Zion&rsquo;s Banner is shown top left, at
the entrance.</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">This past month, John Brown, Victor Carrillo
and I (and a full Zion team) attended the <B>NRB</B> (National Religious Broadcasters) Convention in Nashville, Tennessee.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"></P>

<!-- Field: Page; Sequence: 2 -->
    <DIV STYLE="margin-top: 12pt; margin-bottom: 6pt; border-bottom: Black 1pt solid"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%; font-size: 10pt"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: center; width: 100%">&nbsp;</TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <DIV STYLE="page-break-before: always; margin-top: 6pt; margin-bottom: 12pt"><TABLE CELLPADDING="0" CELLSPACING="0" STYLE="width: 100%"><TR><TD STYLE="text-align: left; width: 50%">&nbsp;</TD><TD STYLE="text-align: right; width: 50%"></TD></TR></TABLE></DIV>
    <!-- Field: /Page -->
<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><IMG SRC="pic3.jpg" ALT=""></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><B>John Brown, Victor G. Carrillo and Richard
J. Rinberg being interviewed on American Family Radio<BR>by Dan Celia at the 2012 NRB Convention</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><B>&nbsp;</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><IMG SRC="pic4.jpg" ALT=""></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><B>John Brown and Richard J. Rinberg
being interviewed on Chuck Crismier&rsquo;s Radio Show<BR>at the 2012 NRB Convention</B></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">John, Victor and I gave a number of interviews.
These were warmly received and resulted in much interest in Zion&rsquo;s work. After the interview on American Family Radio, interviewer
Dan Celia commented: &ldquo;I have gotten an enormous amount of positive responses to the interview&rdquo;.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Zion&rsquo;s President and Chief Operating
Officer, Victor G. Carrillo, left the <B>NRB Convention</B> to attend the <B>NAPE Expo </B>in Houston, Texas - the world&rsquo;s
largest prospect expo with over 1,600 booths and 16,000 attendees. Victor reported that this year was the first year that there
was a special program for the International Pavilion that offered an informative opening Global Briefing Session with a separate
international exhibition of over 75 exhibitors and detailed presentations of opportunities that span over 35 countries, including
Israel, Cyprus, and Lebanon.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">During the opening Global Briefing Session,
a representative of Noble Energy, a Houston-based Independent oil and gas company, reported that to date, Noble has encountered
world class discoveries of natural gas in its Mediterranean exploration areas, offshore Israel and Cyprus.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">At NAPE Expo, Victor established a number of
contacts that may be very helpful in Zion&rsquo;s future exploration efforts in Israel.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center"><I>&ldquo;In your good pleasure, make Zion prosper...&rdquo;</I></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">Psalm 51:18</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: center">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Thank you for your support of Zion</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Shalom from Israel</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">Richard Rinberg</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">CEO of Zion Oil &amp; Gas, Inc.</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">www.zionoil.com</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify"></P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">&nbsp;</P>

<P STYLE="font: 10pt Times New Roman, Times, Serif; margin: 0; text-align: justify">FORWARD LOOKING STATEMENTS: Statements in this
communication that are not historical fact, including statements regarding Zion&rsquo;s planned operations, anticipated attributes
of geological strata comprising our license areas, the presence or recoverability of hydrocarbons, plans to perform seismic surveys,
the timing of these surveys, the impact of these surveys on identifying drilling prospects, the grant of applied-for exploration
license and permits, the sufficiency of cash reserves, timing and potential results thereof and plans contingent thereon are forward-looking
statements as defined in the &ldquo;Safe Harbor&rdquo; provisions of the Private Securities Litigation Reform Act of 1995. These
forward looking statements are based on assumptions that are subject to significant known and unknown risks, uncertainties and
other unpredictable factors, many of which are described in Zion&rsquo;s periodic reports filed with the SEC and are beyond Zion&rsquo;s
control. These risks could cause Zion&rsquo;s actual performance to differ materially from the results predicted by these forward-looking
statements. Zion can give no assurance that the expectations reflected in these statements will prove to be correct and assumes
no responsibility to update these statements.</P>
